        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 8:39AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 839 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty winds along an
outflow boundary extending from near Eliasville to 6 miles southeast
of Fort Griffin to 6 miles northwest of Avoca. Movement was south at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Stamford, Anson, Albany, Hawley, Lueders, Moran, Ibex, Hamby, Nugent,
Avoca, Impact, Funston, Mccarty Lake, Lake Fort Phantom Hill, Us-
283 Near The Callahan-Shackelford County Line, Us-
180 Near The Shackelford-
Stephens County Line, The Intersection Of Us-
180 And Farm Road 600, Hodges, Big Country Baptist Assembly, and
Truby.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
